<div className="merged-type-separator"></div>

<div className="as-h1">

## SortOrder {#sortorder}

</div>

<span title="Type: Type" style={{"display":"inline-flex","alignItems":"center","padding":"0.125rem 0.5rem","backgroundColor":"transparent","color":"rgb(102, 102, 102)","border":"1px solid rgb(102, 102, 102)","borderRadius":"0.375rem","fontSize":"0.575rem","fontWeight":"600","position":"relative","bottom":"20px"}}>Type</span>

> **SortOrder** = \`"asc"\` \\| \`"desc"\`

Sort order type for orderBy function.

---

## Since

2.0.0"
`;

exports[`Admonitions — @info, @note, @deprecated > retry (@info, @throws, merged interface) 1`] = `
"# retry()

> **retry**\\<\`T\`\\>(\`fn\`, \`options\`): \`Promise\`\\<\`T\`\\>

Retries an async function with configurable backoff and error filtering.

:::info[WHY WRAPPING NATIVE?]

We prefer to wrap this to improve resilience against transient failures, adhering to **Fail Fast** principles by managing retries declaratively. See [Design Philosophy](/guide/contribution/design-principles/design-philosophy/)

:::


---

## Type Parameters

### T: \`T\`

The return type of the function.

---

## Parameters

### fn: \`() => Promise<T>\`

The async function to retry.

### options: <TypeRef>[RetryOptions](#retryoptions) = &#123;&#125;</TypeRef>

Retry configuration options.

---

## Returns: \`Promise<T>\`

Promise that resolves to the function's return value.


---

## Throws

The last error thrown by \`fn\` if all retries fail.

---

## Since

1.1.0

---

## Performance

Exponential backoff with \`maxDelay\` cap prevents excessive wait times.
             Jitter prevents thundering herd problem in distributed systems.

---

## Also known as

<AlsoKnownAs data={{"lodash":null,"ramda":null,"radashi":{"name":"retry","group":"Async"},"remeda":null,"moderndash":{"name":"retry","group":"Promise"},"antfu":null,"effect":{"name":"retry","group":"Schedule"},"es-toolkit":null,"python":{"name":"retry","group":"tenacity"},"kotlin":null}} />


---

## Example

\`\`\`typescript
const result = await retry(() => fetchData(), { attempts: 3 });

const result = await retry(() => apiCall(), {
  attempts: 5,
  delay: 1000,
  backoff: 2,
  jitter: 0.5,
  until: (error) => error.code !== 'PERMANENT_ERROR'
});
\`\`\`

---

## How it works?

Retries a failed async function with configurable backoff and jitter.
Exponential backoff increases delay between attempts — jitter adds randomness to prevent thundering herd.
\`\`\`mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant R as retry
    participant F as fn()
    
    R->>F: attempt 1
    F-->>R: ❌ error
    Note right of R: ⏳ delay (1000ms)
    R->>F: attempt 2
    F-->>R: ❌ error
    Note right of R: ⏳ delay × backoff (2000ms)
    R->>F: attempt 3
    F-->>R: ✅ success
\`\`\`

### Exponential Backoff
<ResponsiveMermaid
  desktop={\`flowchart LR
    A["❌ Attempt 1"] -->|"1000ms"| B["❌ Attempt 2"]
    B -->|"2000ms"| C["❌ Attempt 3"]
    C -->|"4000ms"| D["✅ Attempt 4"]\`}
  mobile={\`flowchart TB
    A["❌ Attempt 1"] -->|"1000ms"| B["❌ Attempt 2"]
    B -->|"2000ms"| C["❌ Attempt 3"]
    C -->|"4000ms"| D["✅ Attempt 4"]\`}
/>

### Jitter Visualization

Jitter adds randomness to delay to avoid synchronized retries:
<ResponsiveMermaid
  desktop={\`flowchart LR
    subgraph "Without Jitter"
        A1["Server 1: 1000ms"] --> B1["1000ms"] --> C1["1000ms"]
        A2["Server 2: 1000ms"] --> B2["1000ms"] --> C2["1000ms"]
    end\`}
  mobile={\`flowchart TB
    subgraph "Without Jitter"
        A1["Server 1: 1000ms"] --> B1["1000ms"] --> C1["1000ms"]
        A2["Server 2: 1000ms"] --> B2["1000ms"] --> C2["1000ms"]
    end\`}
/>

<ResponsiveMermaid
  desktop={\`flowchart LR
    subgraph "With Jitter (0.5)"
        A3["Server 1: 1200ms"] --> B3["1800ms"] --> C3["2100ms"]
        A4["Server 2: 900ms"] --> B4["2200ms"] --> C4["1950ms"]
    end\`}
  mobile={\`flowchart TB
    subgraph "With Jitter (0.5)"
        A3["Server 1: 1200ms"] --> B3["1800ms"] --> C3["2100ms"]
        A4["Server 2: 900ms"] --> B4["2200ms"] --> C4["1950ms"]
    end\`}
/>

### Until (Error Filter)

The \`until\` option aborts retry if error is permanent:
<ResponsiveMermaid
  desktop={\`flowchart LR
    A["❌ TEMPORARY_ERROR"] -->|"retry"| B["❌ PERMANENT_ERROR"]
    B -->|"until returns false"| C["⛔ abort, throw"]\`}
  mobile={\`flowchart TB
    A["❌ TEMPORARY_ERROR"] -->|"retry"| B["❌ PERMANENT_ERROR"]
    B -->|"until returns false"| C["⛔ abort, throw"]\`}
/>

---

## Use Cases

### Handle network failures gracefully 📌

Implement robust retry logic for network operations with exponential backoff.
Essential for handling transient network issues and improving reliability.

